  "title": "React dependency?",
  "body": "Hi, \r\n\r\nI installed this library in a Meteor/Blaze app and got the following exception:\r\n\r\n```\r\nUnable to resolve some modules:\r\n  \"react\" in /Users/user/repos/my_app/node_modules/instantsearch.js/dist-es5-module/src/widgets/toggle/toggle.js (web.browser)\r\n  \"react-dom\" in /Users/user/repos/my_app/node_modules/instantsearch.js/dist-es5-module/src/widgets/toggle/toggle.js (web.browser)\r\n                                              \r\nIf you notice problems related to these missing modules, consider running:\r\n                                              \r\n  meteor npm install --save react react-dom  \r\n```\r\nIt works if I install it but do I really need to? I am not using react otherwise so prefer not having to install it just for instantsearch.\r\n\r\nThanks.\r\n\r\n**Edit**: When I look into components I now see that most of them use React. I thought this project were meant for vanilla Javascript users where react-instantsearch is for React users.\r\n",
